election_record.label: New York 1820 State Senate, Western District

sub_unit.name: Allegany
sub_unit.note: Oliver Forward received 1 vote as Oliver Ford.

sub_unit.name: Pike
sub_unit.note: Nathan Williams received 154 votes as Nathaniel Williams.

sub_unit.name: Rushford
sub_unit.note: Philetus Swift received 75 votes as Philetus.

sub_unit.name: Little Valley
sub_unit.note: The votes from Little Valley in Cattaraugus County were not included in the published Official Canvass of votes but were reported in a footnote: "were returned in figures and not in words at length."

sub_unit.name: Cayuga
sub_unit.note: Nathaniel Garrow received 1 vote as Nath. Garrow.

sub_unit.name: Genesee
sub_unit.note: Nathan Williams received 1 vote as Nathaniel Williams.
Elijah Miles received 1 vote as Elijah Mills.

sub_unit.name: Oswego
sub_unit.note: The New York Statesman June 6, 1820 lists a total of 292 votes for Ephraim Hart in Oswego County, but the town totals add up to 293.

sub_unit.name: Steuben
sub_unit.note: Nathan Williams received 1 vote as Nahan Williams.

sub_unit.name: Tioga
sub_unit.note: Nathan Williams received 1 vote as Nathaiel Williams.
